<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1845" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1845">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.04/4.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">McGoodwin</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 90.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 212
                            of July 14th last with which you enclose with translation a copy of the
                            note from the Venezuelan Minister of Foreign Affairs advising you that
                            the Government of Venezuela has granted unrestricted and permanent
                            permission to all salaried consular officers of the United States to
                            visit ships of whatever nationality bound for ports in the United
                            States. Porto Rico and Colon.</p>
                        <pb facs="1213" n="1097" xml:id="pg_1097"/>
                        <p>The Department desires that you convey to the Venezuelan Foreign Office
                            an expression of its sincere appreciation of the action taken by the
                            Government of Venezuela.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>